President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate six individuals for key roles in his administration. The nominees are as follows:

1. Alexander Hoehn-Saric: Nominee for Chair of the Consumer Product Safety Commission. He currently serves as Chief Counsel for Communications and Consumer Protection for the U.S. House of Representatives Committee on Energy & Commerce.

2. Mary Boyle: Nominee for Commissioner of the Consumer Product Safety Commission. She is currently the Executive Director of the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission and has extensive experience in policy, administration, and legal matters.

3. Gerald W. Fauth III: Nominee for Member of the National Mediation Board. He currently serves as Chairman of the National Mediation Board and has 40 years of experience in the transportation industry.

4. Linda Puchala: Nominee for Member of the National Mediation Board. She has been serving as a Member of the National Mediation Board since 2009 and has prior experience in labor relations.

5. Betty Y. Jang: Nominee for Member of the Board of Trustees of the Harry S. Truman Scholarship Foundation. She is an executive with over 25 years of legal, compliance, and leadership experience.

6. Audrey K. Schuster: Nominee for Member of the Board of Trustees of the Harry S. Truman Scholarship Foundation. She has been actively involved in the education and family service community for over 30 years.

These nominees bring a diverse range of experience and expertise to their respective roles and will play important roles in the Biden administration's efforts to protect consumers, promote labor relations, and support education and scholarship programs.